Plants of North Carolina, USA

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poiret) Brummitt

North Carolina: Swain County
35.49966° Latitude -083.62101° Longitude          5190 Ft. Elevation
Quadrangle: Noland Creek                      Hazel Creek Watershed

Great Smoky Mountains National Park. At High Rocks.
High elevation rocky hilltop. Associates include: *Quercus alba*, *Fagus grandifolia*, *Prunus pensylvanica*, *Kalmia latifolia*, *Sambucus pubens*, *Corylus cornuta*, *Andropogon gerardii*, and *Carex trisperma*.
